result.name: Koh-I-Noor Indian Restaurant

reviews.text:
Writing the review, just a few minutes after finishing dinner now. One of the worst experiences ever. Chicken starter we ordered was not cooked and that was returned. 
They had charged in full for the item. On discussion, the manager was downright rude and was not ready to accept our complaint. She not only charged full for uncooked chicken but also rude in her attitude saying she cannot adjust the bill because the dish was tasted and she is not the owner to decide. We tried to make her understand without tasting we wouldn't know it's uncooked but she was least bothered and very rude.

Great tasting food, very good service and friendly staff. We ordered to much (or own fault!) But it was so delicious that we pretty much finished it. 😁 The lamb Rogan Josh was really good, but if you like something non spicy, the Palak paneer was perfect!  This place is also great value for money... We will be going back there very soon.. 👍
Hard to find. Look for the signs. Great food great ambience. Nice staff and service is good.
Location is a bit difficult to find. But food and atmosphere is top notch.
Food is good. Friendly staff
